{"timestamp": "2025-12-12 15:56:14.603406", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Anomaly detected**\\n\\n- A ping from `router_dist_1_2` to `router_dist_2_1` (and vice‑versa) fails with **“Network is unreachable.”**  \\n- The two routers are the only devices that are directly connected on the 172.16.0.0/31 segment, so this failure indicates a problem on the inter‑router link.\\n\\n**Faulty devices**\\n\\n| Device | Interface | IP address | Expected /31 network |\\n|--------|-----------|------------|----------------------|\\n| `router_dist_1_2` | eth0 | 172.16.0.9/31 | 172.16.0.8/31 (neighbour 172.16.0.8) |\\n| `router_dist_2_1` | eth0 | 172.16.0.11/31 | 172.16.0.10/31 (neighbour 172.16.0.10) |\\n\\nBoth routers are configured with IPs that belong to **different /31 networks**.  \\nThe route tables confirm this mismatch:\\n\\n- `router_dist_1_2` routes 10.1.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.8 (its neighbour on eth0).\\n- `router_dist_2_1` routes 10.2.2.0/24 via 172.16.0.10 (its neighbour on eth0).\\n\\nBecause the two routers are on separate /31 subnets, they cannot reach each other, which is why the ping fails.\\n\\n**Root cause**\\n\\nThe inter‑router link is mis‑configured: the IP addresses on `eth0` of `router_dist_1_2` and `router_dist_2_1` are not on the same /31 network. This mis‑configuration prevents any traffic from traversing the link, leading to the observed connectivity failure., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='e56d0d9b-da80-44b7-8157-c85863d345d4'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
